    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The return of cultural property, such as looted artwork or historic artifacts, to its country or culture of origin. From the late 20th century into the 21st, the issue of and debates surrounding repatriation has grown as countries assess their laws related to cultural property, and their histories related to colonialism. </Note_Text>
